Nathan Adler was an American psychoanalyst, former lecturer in Criminology and Psychology at UC Berkeley, and a former professor of clinical psychology at the California School of Professional Psychology at Berkeley/Alameda. Between 1965 and 1970 he conducted extensive clinical studies of drug users in the San Francisco Bay area. He authored the book "The Underground Stream: New Lifestyles and the Antinomian Personality." In his youth, he wrote for several prominent leftist journals in New York.
